mainmenu "Alif CRC Test Configuration"

config TEST_CRC_8
	bool "Test CRC 8-bit CCITT algorithm"
	help
	  This configuration enables comprehensive test cases for the 8-bit CRC
	  CCITT algorithm implementation. The tests cover basic CRC computation,
	  reflection modes, byte and bit swapping options, and output inversion
	  capabilities to ensure robust functionality across various use cases.

config TEST_CRC_16
	bool "Test CRC 16-bit CCITT algorithm"
	help
	  This configuration enables comprehensive test cases for the 16-bit CRC
	  CCITT algorithm implementation. The tests cover basic CRC computation,
	  reflection modes, byte and bit swapping options, and output inversion
	  capabilities to ensure robust functionality across various use cases.

config TEST_CRC_32
	bool "Test CRC 32-bit algorithm"
	help
	  This configuration enables comprehensive test cases for the 32-bit CRC
	  algorithm implementation using the standard polynomial (0x04C11DB7).
	  The tests validate basic CRC computation, reflection modes, byte and bit
	  swapping options, output inversion, and compatibility with common
	  CRC-32 applications.

config TEST_CRC_32_CUSTOM_POLY
	bool "Test CRC 32-bit custom polynomial algorithm"
	help
	  This configuration enables test cases for the 32-bit CRC algorithm with
	  user-defined custom polynomials. It validates the ability to configure
	  and use non-standard polynomials (such as 0x2CEEA6C8) while testing
	  basic CRC computation, reflection modes, swapping options, and output
	  inversion for custom applications.

config TEST_CRC_32C
	bool "Test CRC-32C (Castagnoli) algorithm"
	help
	  This configuration enables test cases for the CRC-32C (Castagnoli)
	  algorithm implementation using polynomial 0x1EDC6F41. CRC-32C is widely
	  used in networking protocols including iSCSI, SCTP, and filesystem
	  integrity checks in ext4 and Btrfs. Tests cover standard operations,
	  reflection, swapping, and inversion modes.

config TEST_CRC_STRESS
	bool "CRC stress and robustness tests"
	help
	  Enable stress tests that exercise driver resilience:
	  repeatability, seed variation, back-to-back operations,
	  boundary conditions, bit-flip sensitivity, parameter
	  orthogonality, and large data handling.

	  If combined with TEST_CRC_32_CUSTOM_POLY or TEST_CRC_32C,
	  dedicated CRC32-family stress vectors are also enabled to
	  validate custom polynomial setup, known-vector matching, and
	  unaligned-tail handling.

source "Kconfig.zephyr"
